concepts/Administration.description: Qdrant exposes administration tools which enable to modify at runtime the behavior of a qdrant instance without changing its configuration manually.

concepts/Configuration.title: Configuration
concepts/Configuration.description: To change or correct Qdrant's behavior, default collection settings, and network interface parameters, you can use the configuration file.

concepts/Filtering.title: Filtering
concepts/Filtering.description: Qdrant allows you to set the conditions to be used when searching or retrieving points.

concepts/Indexing.title: Indexing
concepts/Indexing.description: A key feature of Qdrant is the effective combination of vector and traditional indexes. It is essential to have this because for vector search to work effectively with filters, having vector index only is not enough. In simpler terms, a vector index speeds up vector search, and payload indexes speed up filtering.

concepts/Optimizer.title: Optimizer
concepts/Optimizer.description: It is much more efficient to apply changes in batches than perform each change individually, as many other databases do. Qdrant here is no exception. Since Qdrant operates with data structures that are not always easy to change, it is sometimes necessary to rebuild those structures completely.

concepts/Payload.title: Payload
concepts/Payload.description: One of the significant features of Qdrant is the ability to store additional information along with vectors.
